# gossip-sdk (vendor/gossip submodule) references vite/client ambient types, imports
# @capacitor/core types, and (via apps/web's vite-plugin-node-polyfills, which auto-shims
# any module using the `process`/`Buffer`/`global` Node globals) needs that plugin's shim
# imports resolvable from inside the submodule too — but it declares none of these as its
# own dependencies. pnpm's default strict, per-package node_modules means it can't resolve
# them otherwise. Hoisting to the true workspace root lets Node/TypeScript/Rollup's upward
# node_modules resolution find them without editing the (vendored, upstream-owned) submodule.
public-hoist-pattern[]=vite
public-hoist-pattern[]=@capacitor/core
public-hoist-pattern[]=vite-plugin-node-polyfills
